The concept behind Atlas is a spell system that takes in blocks and items as inputs and produces unique yet consistent spells and enchantments based on them

The vanilla enchanting system is to be overwritten by this system by adding a modifier to spell construction that enables it to stick to items / armour
Spells are otherwise books that when right-clicked do something, certain spells stick to the ground and trigger upon being walked upon, some spells trigger when redstone is activated e.t.c
The system is built upon Gen-AI much like Neal.fun and will combine new spells from a pool of mythic mobs skills that are hand-crafted therefore ensuring balance

The Core:

- Spell Element (Can be anything, no arbitrary categorisations of "elements")
- Delivery system (Projectile, Area, Line, Enchantment, Self-buff, Summon, Utility)

Modifiers:

- Speed of spell
- Duration
- Size
- Chain / pull
- Piercing?
- Bounce
- Catalyst (modify strength)